 class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4399891\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4399891\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 17, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104naa1689059984146.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/naa1689059984146.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/naa1689059984146.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"naa1689059984146\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This option specifies how Uniface tries to check out Sentinel licenses.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"naa1689059984146__p_d141104e1_d141105e1_d141106e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_LOAD=</code>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">S</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">sentinel</code> |\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">snt</code> } | {<code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code>} {<code class=\"ph codeph\">R</code>}\n\t\t\t\t{<code class=\"ph codeph\">G</code>} {<code class=\"ph codeph\">9</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">10</code>}</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"naa1689059984146__ul_u51_ywb_xvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"naa1689059984146__li_d49853e1_d49854e1_d49855e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">S</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">sentinel</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">snt</code>—this is the\n\t\t\t\tdefault and is equivalent to <code class=\"ph codeph\">CRG</code> on Windows and Linux and\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">CR</code> on other platforms. Commuter licenses are tried first, then\n\t\t\t\tthe RMS License Manager is tried. If that fails, on Windows and Linux Grace licenses\n\t\t\t\tare tried. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"naa1689059984146__li_d49856e1_d49857e1_d49858e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code>—instructs Uniface to look for a Commuter license. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"naa1689059984146__li_d49859e1_d49860e1_d49861e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">R</code>—instructs Uniface to look for a license from the RMS License\n\t\t\t\tManager(s). </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"naa1689059984146__li_d49862e1_d49863e1_d49864e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">G</code>—instructs Uniface to look for a Grace license. Grace licenses are\n\t\t\t\tgranted automatically, if included in your Entitlement. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"naa1689059984146__li_d49865e1_d49866e1_d49867e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">9</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">10</code>—instructs Uniface to use Sentinel version 9\n\t\t\t\tor version 10. Both versions of the Sentinel libraries are included in the product.\n\t\t\t\tVersion 9 is set by default, unless a Cloud LM license is used, which will set this\n\t\t\t\tto <code class=\"ph codeph\">10</code>. <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"naa1689059984146__note_pbh_2dy_nvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The user can use\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_LOAD=10</code> on all OS platforms.</div></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"naa1689059984146__p_d141107e1_d141108e1_d141109e1\">If <code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_LICENSE_FILE</code> specifies an RMS\n\t\t\tLicense Manager, you can specify one or more single letters (<code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code>,\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">R</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">G</code>) to control which type of license is tried\n\t\t\tand the order in which Uniface attempts to check out a license.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"naa1689059984146__p_d141110e1_d141111e1_d141112e1\">For example, you may wish to disable Commuter and/or\n\t\t\tGrace licenses if you are sure you will not be needing these license types. This can\n\t\t\timprove startup performance by eliminating unnecessary checks. To do so, set\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_LOAD=R</code>. This instructs Uniface to only check out a license from\n\t\t\tthe RMS License Manager.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"naa1689059984146__p_d141113e1_d141114e1_d141115e1\">Only disable Grace when the application is running\n\t\t\ton the same machine as the RMS License Manager. This is to ensure that no network issues\n\t\t\twill cause the RMS License Manager to become unavailable.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"naa1689059984146__note_w472ab1b5c13c15_w473ab1b5c13_w474ab1b5_w475ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span>  Grace licenses are\n\t\t\tsupported only on Windows and Linux.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"naa1689059984146__p_d141116e1_d141117e1_d141118e1\">If you specify <code class=\"ph codeph\">Sentinel</code> or\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">SNT</code>, that must be the only option. When using single letters, you\n\t\t\tcan specify more than one. This disables certain license types, for example\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">CR</code> to disable Grace licenses, or <code class=\"ph codeph\">RG</code> to disable\n\t\t\tCommuter Licenses. If you are specifying the Sentinel version, this must be at the end,\n\t\t\tfor example <code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_LOAD=CR10</code> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LM_LOAD=Sentinel 10</span>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4399891\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4399891\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "LM_LOAD Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 17, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 This option specifies how Uniface tries to check out Sentinel licenses. LM_LOAD= { S | sentinel | snt } | { C } { R } { G } { 9 | 10 } S | sentinel | snt —this is the default and is equivalent to CRG on Windows and Linux and CR on other platforms. Commuter licenses are tried first, then the RMS License Manager is tried. If that fails, on Windows and Linux Grace licenses are tried. C —instructs Uniface to look for a Commuter license. R —instructs Uniface to look for a license from the RMS License Manager(s). G —instructs Uniface to look for a Grace license. Grace licenses are granted automatically, if included in your Entitlement. 9 | 10 —instructs Uniface to use Sentinel version 9 or version 10. Both versions of the Sentinel libraries are included in the product. Version 9 is set by default, unless a Cloud LM license is used, which will set this to 10 . Note: The user can use LM_LOAD=10 on all OS platforms. If LM_LICENSE_FILE specifies an RMS License Manager, you can specify one or more single letters ( C , R , G ) to control which type of license is tried and the order in which Uniface attempts to check out a license. For example, you may wish to disable Commuter and/or Grace licenses if you are sure you will not be needing these license types. This can improve startup performance by eliminating unnecessary checks. To do so, set LM_LOAD=R . This instructs Uniface to only check out a license from the RMS License Manager. Only disable Grace when the application is running on the same machine as the RMS License Manager. This is to ensure that no network issues will cause the RMS License Manager to become unavailable. Note: Grace licenses are supported only on Windows and Linux. If you specify Sentinel or SNT , that must be the only option. When using single letters, you can specify more than one. This disables certain license types, for example CR to disable Grace licenses, or RG to disable Commuter Licenses. If you are specifying the Sentinel version, this must be at the end, for example LM_LOAD=CR10 or LM_LOAD=Sentinel 10 . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}